  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of the pilot study is to compare new laryngoscopes for infants by assessing the
      equipment best suited to assist the intubation, with the best overview, shortest time to
      intubation and use these numbers to make a sample size calculation for the full protocol. The
      investigators hypothesis is that the Storz videolaryngoscope® has a better success rate than
      infants (&lt;2 years). The patients will be optimally anaesthetized with neuromuscular blockade
      for the intubation. All patient will be evaluated with af Macintosh blade laryngoscope, with
      an Airtraq® or a Storz videolaryngoscope®, and finally intubated with the other one of the
      later, which the patient was randomized to.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
